com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class TokenizeRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.TokenizeRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RecordKeyProvider, SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serializable

    public class TokenizeRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
implements RecordKeyProvider
    Generates match tokens for a base object record that has been updated or inserted. If the record has been tokenized previously, this API can be used to regenerate the match tokens for the record.

    Required Parameters:

    • setRecordKey(RecordKey) - Sets the key of the record for which tokens need to be generated.
    • setActionType(String) - Action type returned from a previous put or cleanse put request.
    • SiperianObjectUid - package or base object.

    Usage Example:

    The following example shows how to generate match tokens for a record with ROWID_OBJECT key 782 using the ADDRESS_UPDATE package:

    TokenizeRequest request = new TokenizeRequest();
    request.setSiperianObjectUid( SiperianObjectType.PACKAGE.makeUid( "ADDRESS_UPDATE" ) );
    RecordKey recordKey = new RecordKey();
    recordKey.setRowid("782");
    request.setRecordKey( recordKey );
    request.setActionType("Insert");
    TokenizeResponse response = (TokenizeResponse) sipClient.process(request);

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    API Pair: TokenizeResponse

    API Group: Data Update/Insert
